1
00:00:10,282 --> 00:00:13,435
You know the kids here aren't like normal kids.

2
00:00:13,948 --> 00:00:15,610
Look after our new friend, Tanrak.

3
00:00:15,820 --> 00:00:16,546
I’m Barth.

4
00:00:16,601 --> 00:00:17,440
Like basketball?

5
00:00:17,575 --> 00:00:19,451
Like the saint. Bartholomew.

6
00:00:19,775 --> 00:00:22,215
It’s Grade 12, second term, and you still got in?

7
00:00:22,840 --> 00:00:23,821
What are you gonna do about it?

8
00:00:25,159 --> 00:00:26,833
Barth! Barth! Barth!

9
00:00:27,087 --> 00:00:29,420
But if you keep behaving like this,

10
00:00:29,890 --> 00:00:31,969
I’ll have to ask you to leave the school.

11
00:00:32,306 --> 00:00:33,609
Do you really believe in God?

12
00:00:33,952 --> 00:00:35,329
I believe God is real.

13
00:00:35,723 --> 00:00:39,391
I believe my parents are with Him up there.

14
00:00:39,872 --> 00:00:43,359
Maybe my God isn’t as kind as yours.

15
00:00:49,049 --> 00:00:51,169
“WHAT MAN AMONG YOU
HAVING A HUNDRED SHEEP

16
00:00:51,194 --> 00:00:52,969
AND LOSING ONE OF THEM

17
00:00:52,994 --> 00:00:55,280
WOULD NOT LEAVE THE NINETY-NINE IN THE DESERT

18
00:00:55,305 --> 00:00:57,591
AND GO AFTER THE LOST ONE UNTIL HE FINDS IT?”

19
00:00:57,616 --> 00:00:59,393
(LUKE 15:4)

20
00:01:03,838 --> 00:01:05,518
Alright, let's go home.

21
00:01:05,885 --> 00:01:07,088
Always causing trouble.

22
00:01:13,687 --> 00:01:14,687
Sit down.

23
00:01:25,589 --> 00:01:27,856
Kongkit was wrong for starting it,

24
00:01:28,827 --> 00:01:30,827
but you two were at fault too.

25
00:01:33,020 --> 00:01:34,569
He was just trying to help me, Father.

26
00:01:36,440 --> 00:01:38,489
It’s good to be kind,

27
00:01:39,249 --> 00:01:40,649
but for something this serious,

28
00:01:40,738 --> 00:01:43,350
you should’ve told me or Master Phak,

29
00:01:43,743 --> 00:01:45,849
not help each other hide it.

30
00:01:47,356 --> 00:01:49,103
What if it had gotten worse?

31
00:01:49,628 --> 00:01:50,700
What would you do then?

32
00:01:53,210 --> 00:01:54,650
I’m sorry, Father.

33
00:02:01,329 --> 00:02:02,329
Barth.

34
00:02:02,979 --> 00:02:04,042
You can go now.

35
00:02:19,251 --> 00:02:22,769
I trusted you to look after the new boy.

36
00:02:23,645 --> 00:02:26,614
I thought you could’ve handled
this better, Tanrak.

37
00:02:28,858 --> 00:02:30,289
I’m really sorry.

38
00:02:33,868 --> 00:02:34,868
From now on,

39
00:02:35,429 --> 00:02:37,720
I hope you’ll take better care of him.

40
00:02:38,913 --> 00:02:40,009
I’m counting on you.

41
00:02:43,278 --> 00:02:44,278
Yes, Father.

42
00:02:48,273 --> 00:02:49,407
Please excuse me.

43
00:03:11,249 --> 00:03:15,714
SCHOLARSHIP STUDENT REPORT BOOK

44
00:04:19,729 --> 00:04:21,906
ANGER IS QUELLED BY PATIENCE.

45
00:04:35,515 --> 00:04:37,386
What are you doing here all alone,
so studious?

46
00:04:43,479 --> 00:04:45,204
I’m not studying. I’m being punished.

47
00:04:46,407 --> 00:04:47,407
Master Phak.

48
00:04:50,807 --> 00:04:51,847
Just call me P'Phak.

49
00:04:52,650 --> 00:04:54,124
We’re only a few years apart.

50
00:04:54,916 --> 00:04:56,439
No need to be so formal all the time.

51
00:05:07,617 --> 00:05:10,408
Hey, if you’re being punished,
take it seriously.

52
00:05:11,765 --> 00:05:12,955
Maybe using up the whole book

53
00:05:13,521 --> 00:05:14,694
will teach you a lesson.

54
00:05:18,255 --> 00:05:19,749
I still don’t know what I did wrong.

55
00:05:20,997 --> 00:05:23,119
Making me write hundreds more lines
won’t change that.

56
00:05:27,635 --> 00:05:30,653
P'Phak! Come play with us.
We’re one short.

57
00:05:30,880 --> 00:05:31,937
Yeah, I’ll be right there.

58
00:05:32,071 --> 00:05:33,769
Okay. Hurry.

59
00:05:36,977 --> 00:05:38,890
Hey, can you play football?

60
00:05:42,399 --> 00:05:45,417
Yeah, but I… don’t know anyone.

61
00:05:46,669 --> 00:05:47,669
So what?

62
00:05:48,230 --> 00:05:49,622
You’re gonna be here for a year.

63
00:05:50,512 --> 00:05:51,947
Don’t you plan to make any friends?

64
00:05:57,723 --> 00:05:59,969
Well, join me if you wanna play.

65
00:06:03,335 --> 00:06:04,335
Here I come.

66
00:06:18,831 --> 00:06:24,701
Lord, bless us and this food
we are about to receive.

67
00:06:24,970 --> 00:06:27,769
In the name of the Father, and of the Son,
and of the Holy Spirit.

68
00:06:28,323 --> 00:06:29,323
Amen.

69
00:06:49,066 --> 00:06:50,066
Up to you.

70
00:06:53,429 --> 00:06:54,429
Barth.

71
00:07:30,652 --> 00:07:31,809
I can sit somewhere else.

72
00:07:32,799 --> 00:07:35,009
Sit here. I was just kidding.

73
00:07:37,019 --> 00:07:38,569
Why would you sit by the trash can?

74
00:07:39,451 --> 00:07:40,451
Sit here.

75
00:07:47,456 --> 00:07:50,125
You know all these kids

76
00:07:50,453 --> 00:07:51,834
are scared that you’ll punch them?

77
00:07:53,675 --> 00:07:55,408
But I’m not scared of you.

78
00:07:56,818 --> 00:07:58,388
Because God teaches us…

79
00:07:59,816 --> 00:08:02,715
Love your neighbor as yourself.

80
00:08:03,977 --> 00:08:05,416
Damn!

81
00:08:07,121 --> 00:08:08,121
Hey, Kong.

82
00:08:08,423 --> 00:08:10,329
Have you ever been punched
by your neighbor?

83
00:08:11,462 --> 00:08:12,835
You’re about to get punched by me.

84
00:08:13,826 --> 00:08:14,946
Eat your food.

85
00:08:16,880 --> 00:08:17,880
Well.

86
00:08:17,961 --> 00:08:19,081
So is it true?

87
00:08:19,470 --> 00:08:21,169
You knocked out a guy at your old school

88
00:08:21,460 --> 00:08:22,470
with one punch?

89
00:08:24,968 --> 00:08:25,968
Yeah.

90
00:08:26,590 --> 00:08:28,729
Damn, a real boxer's move.

91
00:08:33,021 --> 00:08:34,409
So if I piss you off,

92
00:08:34,836 --> 00:08:35,840
will you punch me?

93
00:08:53,823 --> 00:08:54,863
Just kidding.

94
00:09:13,617 --> 00:09:14,617
Barth.

95
00:09:15,708 --> 00:09:17,186
Were you mad about them teasing you?

96
00:09:19,861 --> 00:09:20,861
No.

97
00:09:22,026 --> 00:09:23,114
I didn’t care. Why?

98
00:09:24,946 --> 00:09:27,649
If you don’t like it, I can tell them.

99
00:09:28,204 --> 00:09:29,529
So there won’t be any trouble.

100
00:10:17,722 --> 00:10:21,178
Tanrak, return these catechism notebooks
to Class 12/1.

101
00:10:23,084 --> 00:10:25,217
Did I... get full marks, Master?

102
00:10:25,427 --> 00:10:27,529
Well, open it and see.

103
00:10:27,895 --> 00:10:30,969
Tell anyone who got less than half
to come see me next Tuesday.

104
00:10:32,061 --> 00:10:33,329
-Yes, Master.
-I’m off to class.

105
00:10:33,701 --> 00:10:34,722
Goodbye, Master.

106
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:54,080
BODIN TUNGWONGWAT

107
00:11:05,836 --> 00:11:08,329
Here, Chris. Collecting full marks, huh?

108
00:11:08,906 --> 00:11:09,714
Not really.

109
00:11:11,058 --> 00:11:12,060
This one’s yours.

110
00:11:28,258 --> 00:11:29,538
Can I move here?

111
00:11:32,876 --> 00:11:34,054
I can’t see the board at all.

112
00:11:36,421 --> 00:11:38,954
That’s Kongdech’s seat. Ask him first.

113
00:11:42,602 --> 00:11:43,802
Can I sit here?

114
00:11:47,518 --> 00:11:48,518
Yeah, sure.

115
00:11:49,336 --> 00:11:50,721
As long as you do well in class.

116
00:12:05,323 --> 00:12:06,333
All right, everyone.

117
00:12:06,383 --> 00:12:08,121
Don’t rush home after class.

118
00:12:08,284 --> 00:12:11,047
Go sign up for this year’s Christmas
activity groups.

119
00:12:11,331 --> 00:12:14,532
Scholarship students without a group
can stay in the same group as last year.

120
00:12:19,375 --> 00:12:21,395
Do we have to do something
for the Christmas party?

121
00:12:24,113 --> 00:12:25,113
Of course.

122
00:12:30,822 --> 00:12:31,844
What do you like doing?

123
00:12:37,289 --> 00:12:38,329
I don’t know.

124
00:12:40,662 --> 00:12:41,969
I don’t like doing anything.

125
00:12:43,087 --> 00:12:44,169
Do I really have to?

126
00:12:45,775 --> 00:12:48,441
Yes, especially as scholarship students.

127
00:12:49,178 --> 00:12:51,225
We have to help out. We have duties.

128
00:12:53,268 --> 00:12:54,826
Oh, Bodin, you don’t have a group yet.

129
00:12:54,937 --> 00:12:56,208
Join the reception team.

130
00:12:56,788 --> 00:12:58,216
If you don’t remember your group,

131
00:12:58,241 --> 00:13:00,409
come check the list with me later.

132
00:13:04,333 --> 00:13:05,414
What group are you in?

133
00:13:06,432 --> 00:13:09,413
Hm? I’m in the choir.

134
00:13:09,724 --> 00:13:10,747
I’ll join you.

135
00:13:13,832 --> 00:13:14,832
You can’t.

136
00:13:15,366 --> 00:13:17,766
Since you don’t like doing anything,

137
00:13:18,345 --> 00:13:20,209
I think the reception team suits you.

138
00:13:20,836 --> 00:13:21,895
You won’t have to do much.

139
00:13:23,474 --> 00:13:24,474
No.

140
00:13:25,502 --> 00:13:28,505
I don’t have any friends.

141
00:13:29,145 --> 00:13:30,254
You’re the only one I know.

142
00:13:38,166 --> 00:13:39,609
You’ll get to know more people

143
00:13:40,739 --> 00:13:42,100
once you start working with them.

144
00:14:24,986 --> 00:14:25,991
What are you doing?

145
00:14:35,918 --> 00:14:37,224
Do you pray like this every day?

146
00:14:40,019 --> 00:14:41,019
No.

147
00:14:41,469 --> 00:14:43,652
I’m here to pray for redemption

148
00:14:46,876 --> 00:14:49,769
Redemption? For what?

149
00:14:57,441 --> 00:15:01,889
Well, I was partly at fault
for what happened to you,

150
00:15:02,944 --> 00:15:04,489
like Father said.

151
00:15:09,661 --> 00:15:11,385
The only wrong thing you did was to help me,

152
00:15:11,410 --> 00:15:12,634
and now you’re screwed too.

153
00:15:19,260 --> 00:15:20,409
Don’t help me next time.

154
00:15:24,259 --> 00:15:26,289
If you feel bad,

155
00:15:27,558 --> 00:15:30,542
then pass your catechism test.

156
00:15:31,715 --> 00:15:35,409
Father assigned me to be your buddy.

157
00:15:37,435 --> 00:15:38,435
Okay?

158
00:15:40,234 --> 00:15:41,249
Then tutor me.

159
00:15:42,799 --> 00:15:43,943
Why should I tutor you?

160
00:15:44,973 --> 00:15:46,033
Because we’re friends.

161
00:15:51,237 --> 00:15:52,278
Since when are we friends?

162
00:16:20,421 --> 00:16:24,889
Barth, can you stop breaking the rules?

163
00:16:25,835 --> 00:16:27,768
I’m gonna get in trouble too.

164
00:16:31,899 --> 00:16:34,006
I didn’t see any sign saying
I couldn’t leave school.

165
00:16:36,522 --> 00:16:38,049
It’s a Magdalene House rule.

166
00:16:45,035 --> 00:16:46,035
Next,

167
00:16:47,930 --> 00:16:52,969
lust means letting desire control us.

168
00:16:54,136 --> 00:16:57,049
What if you can’t stop it?

169
00:17:01,204 --> 00:17:02,219
Then you fight it.

170
00:17:06,902 --> 00:17:07,942
Why fight it?

171
00:17:09,053 --> 00:17:11,005
Have you tried this roti in front of the school?

172
00:17:18,548 --> 00:17:19,818
Go off topic again,

173
00:17:20,156 --> 00:17:22,889
and I won’t tutor you anymore.

174
00:17:25,511 --> 00:17:26,511
Yes, sir.

175
00:17:33,823 --> 00:17:34,823
Want some?

176
00:17:35,986 --> 00:17:36,986
Come on.

177
00:17:38,192 --> 00:17:39,194
Just a bite.

178
00:17:57,210 --> 00:18:00,169
Hurry up or I’ll be late for evening prayer.

179
00:18:05,522 --> 00:18:07,130
Let me see.
What are you even looking at?

180
00:18:10,055 --> 00:18:11,249
There are three people.

181
00:18:11,343 --> 00:18:13,225
The Believer, the Lover, and the Lost One.

182
00:18:13,941 --> 00:18:16,249
One always tells the truth.

183
00:18:16,532 --> 00:18:18,649
One sometimes tells the truth
and sometimes lies.

184
00:18:19,405 --> 00:18:21,005
And one always lies.

185
00:18:21,587 --> 00:18:23,849
The Believer says
the Lover always tells the truth.

186
00:18:24,257 --> 00:18:26,529
The Lover says
the Lost One always lies.

187
00:18:27,383 --> 00:18:30,049
The Lost One says
the Believer doesn’t always tell the truth.

188
00:18:33,713 --> 00:18:37,713
So which one lies
and which one tells the truth?

189
00:18:51,298 --> 00:18:52,298
Seriously?

190
00:18:53,143 --> 00:18:54,535
Isn’t your life stressful enough?

191
00:18:55,479 --> 00:18:56,700
Why are you doing this stuff?

192
00:19:00,918 --> 00:19:01,983
None of your business.

193
00:19:10,918 --> 00:19:12,423
Okay. Off you go, everyone.

194
00:19:17,707 --> 00:19:18,827
Kong, come on.

195
00:19:38,858 --> 00:19:40,152
RECEPTION TEAM

196
00:19:46,435 --> 00:19:47,435
Pairat.

197
00:19:47,547 --> 00:19:48,547
Yes.

198
00:19:48,793 --> 00:19:49,657
Korawit.

199
00:19:49,718 --> 00:19:50,718
Here.

200
00:19:51,285 --> 00:19:52,285
Bodin.

201
00:19:53,779 --> 00:19:54,779
Bodin.

202
00:19:57,867 --> 00:19:58,987
Where’s Bodin?

203
00:19:59,320 --> 00:20:00,320
No idea.

204
00:20:00,757 --> 00:20:05,842
Angels we have heard on high

205
00:20:05,991 --> 00:20:10,359
Sweetly singing o’er the plains

206
00:20:10,806 --> 00:20:15,947
And the mountains in reply

207
00:20:16,096 --> 00:20:20,626
Echoing their joyous strains

208
00:20:21,237 --> 00:20:36,263
Gloria in excelsis Deo

209
00:20:39,935 --> 00:20:41,105
Are you looking for someone?

210
00:20:44,576 --> 00:20:45,576
Well…

211
00:20:47,472 --> 00:20:49,716
Someone told me I was in this group.

212
00:20:51,422 --> 00:20:52,431
My name’s Bodin.

213
00:20:53,906 --> 00:20:54,906
Really?

214
00:20:58,986 --> 00:21:00,409
It’s not here. There’s no Bodin.

215
00:21:05,441 --> 00:21:08,311
They said they asked Tanrak
to pass on the message.

216
00:21:15,563 --> 00:21:16,569
What’s going on, Tanrak?

217
00:21:22,257 --> 00:21:25,050
I forgot. Sorry, Master.

218
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:28,929
That’s okay. Can you sing?

219
00:21:32,833 --> 00:21:35,009
If I can’t, can I help carry things instead?

220
00:21:37,017 --> 00:21:38,647
We all have to help carry things anyway.

221
00:21:38,860 --> 00:21:41,569
All right. Let's hear you sing first.

222
00:21:42,031 --> 00:21:43,337
Maybe we’ll get a new member.

223
00:21:44,631 --> 00:21:45,751
Come up front.

224
00:21:46,343 --> 00:21:47,382
Put your bag down.

225
00:21:49,032 --> 00:21:50,032
What song?

226
00:21:50,481 --> 00:21:51,752
I’ll have someone play for you.

227
00:21:52,210 --> 00:21:53,250
“Before,” please.

228
00:21:53,610 --> 00:21:54,729
“Before” by Modern Dog?

229
00:21:55,056 --> 00:21:56,056
Yes.

230
00:21:56,305 --> 00:21:57,305
Okay.

231
00:21:58,561 --> 00:21:59,729
Give him the chords.

232
00:22:01,058 --> 00:22:02,074
Something like this.

233
00:22:05,048 --> 00:22:08,736
My heart had had no one

234
00:22:09,337 --> 00:22:12,209
Until your love entered

235
00:22:12,502 --> 00:22:17,249
Filling my eyes bright with colors

236
00:22:17,810 --> 00:22:21,289
My side had had no one

237
00:22:21,666 --> 00:22:24,529
Until your love had mercy

238
00:22:25,145 --> 00:22:29,489
To empower me to keep going

239
00:22:30,034 --> 00:22:38,389
In this cruel world

240
00:22:42,591 --> 00:22:43,889
Okay. Wow, that was great!

241
00:22:43,927 --> 00:22:44,969
Give him a hand.

242
00:22:48,790 --> 00:22:49,809
You sing well.

243
00:22:51,857 --> 00:22:53,209
In that case,

244
00:22:53,609 --> 00:22:55,929
you can be in the same part as Tanrak.

245
00:22:56,631 --> 00:22:58,089
He can help train you.

246
00:22:58,861 --> 00:23:00,369
I’m counting on you, Tanrak.

247
00:23:00,662 --> 00:23:01,470
Okay.

248
00:23:01,513 --> 00:23:02,807
Go on. Have a seat.

249
00:23:03,586 --> 00:23:04,595
That chair is fine.

250
00:23:06,405 --> 00:23:08,849
You know the song we’re rehearsing, right?

251
00:23:09,706 --> 00:23:10,462
Yes.

252
00:23:10,529 --> 00:23:12,813
Good. Then let’s go again, everyone.

253
00:23:13,389 --> 00:23:28,162
Gloria in excelsis Deo

254
00:23:28,630 --> 00:23:34,581
Gloria in excelsis Deo

255
00:23:40,765 --> 00:23:43,306
Tanrak, tidy up the room and lock it for me.

256
00:23:43,946 --> 00:23:44,946
Yes, Master.

257
00:23:45,396 --> 00:23:46,405
Bodin, help him out.

258
00:23:46,478 --> 00:23:47,478
Yes.

259
00:24:00,767 --> 00:24:01,767
Who’s this?

260
00:24:04,714 --> 00:24:06,050
Saint Cecilia.

261
00:24:10,524 --> 00:24:13,369
The one who sang when she died?

262
00:24:15,108 --> 00:24:17,889
She sang in her heart, even as she died.

263
00:24:19,816 --> 00:24:22,002
That’s why she became
the patron saint of music.

264
00:24:30,355 --> 00:24:32,203
If she sang in her heart,
who would hear it?

265
00:24:36,116 --> 00:24:37,649
God always hears us.

266
00:24:49,817 --> 00:24:51,421
Do you know every saint or something?

267
00:24:52,467 --> 00:24:53,269
Oops!

268
00:25:11,529 --> 00:25:12,569
"Tan Kham Wa Rak"

269
00:25:13,985 --> 00:25:15,795
"There is a truth I want you to know"

270
00:25:15,918 --> 00:25:18,033
"Meanings words seem to hold"

271
00:25:19,245 --> 00:25:20,809
What song is this? I’ve never heard it.

272
00:25:24,972 --> 00:25:29,635
Tan Kham Wa Rak. Tanrak.

273
00:25:35,126 --> 00:25:36,722
Why are you named Tanrak?

274
00:25:46,816 --> 00:25:47,816
Huh?

275
00:26:10,544 --> 00:26:12,611
So... Why are you named Tanrak?

276
00:26:18,304 --> 00:26:20,541
Tan, where’s Kongdech?

277
00:26:21,588 --> 00:26:24,040
He’s probably at the farm plot.

278
00:26:24,298 --> 00:26:25,729
Oh. I thought you were together.

279
00:26:26,427 --> 00:26:27,432
Come on, guys.

280
00:26:27,665 --> 00:26:29,329
Let’s help Kong at the farm plot.

281
00:26:43,220 --> 00:26:44,820
My mom had a hard time having a child.

282
00:26:45,977 --> 00:26:47,249
So she came here to pray.

283
00:26:48,330 --> 00:26:51,527
When she had me, she named me...

284
00:26:52,517 --> 00:26:53,520
Tanrak.

285
00:26:55,347 --> 00:26:59,049
Because I was a symbol of the love

286
00:27:00,044 --> 00:27:01,129
the Holy Mother gave her.

287
00:27:20,115 --> 00:27:24,260
My mom offered this rosary herself.

288
00:27:27,830 --> 00:27:29,409
When I miss her,

289
00:27:31,021 --> 00:27:32,021
I come here.

290
00:27:35,127 --> 00:27:37,489
And I tell the Holy Mother…

291
00:27:39,172 --> 00:27:43,225
if I ever get to heaven,

292
00:27:44,977 --> 00:27:46,649
please take me to my parents.

293
00:28:07,113 --> 00:28:08,809
Next time I can come here with you.

294
00:28:25,699 --> 00:28:26,699
Tanrak,

295
00:28:28,287 --> 00:28:29,287
I'll help.

296
00:28:40,528 --> 00:28:42,787
Since when are Tan and Barth best buds?

297
00:28:43,233 --> 00:28:46,422
Yeah. When did they become close friends, Kong?

298
00:28:47,867 --> 00:28:49,204
If you wanna know, ask them.

299
00:28:49,835 --> 00:28:52,684
Oh, Mr. Kong. I thought you’d know.

300
00:28:52,850 --> 00:28:54,564
You’re Tan’s closest friend, aren’t you?

301
00:29:06,948 --> 00:29:07,980
Hello, Teacher.

302
00:29:08,232 --> 00:29:09,232
Hello.

303
00:29:09,698 --> 00:29:11,378
What? Where did it go?

304
00:29:12,988 --> 00:29:15,121
Boys, come help me look at this.

305
00:29:16,262 --> 00:29:17,262
Go.

306
00:29:17,403 --> 00:29:20,859
I’m trying to save it, but it won’t work.
What do I do?

307
00:29:23,095 --> 00:29:24,534
It’s gone now.

308
00:29:26,609 --> 00:29:28,389
- This drive can’t burn discs.
- Oh.

309
00:29:28,732 --> 00:29:30,484
It’s a CD-ROM. It only reads them.

310
00:29:31,636 --> 00:29:34,169
What? But I need to save it on a disc.

311
00:29:34,194 --> 00:29:35,082
How am I supposed to do that?

312
00:29:35,107 --> 00:29:36,644
Come look at it for me.

313
00:29:36,669 --> 00:29:37,684
Come here. Sit down.

314
00:29:41,239 --> 00:29:42,804
It won’t save at all.

315
00:29:46,838 --> 00:29:49,599
Oh, the file’s too big.

316
00:29:50,372 --> 00:29:52,041
You’ll need to split it across two discs.

317
00:29:52,401 --> 00:29:55,254
Well, the academic department

318
00:29:55,279 --> 00:29:57,904
told us to stop submitting paper copies
and send files instead.

319
00:29:57,929 --> 00:30:00,662
And those are all the students’ projects.

320
00:30:01,138 --> 00:30:02,564
I’m not very good at this.

321
00:30:03,047 --> 00:30:04,577
If your files disappear,

322
00:30:04,948 --> 00:30:07,124
I’m dead. Totally dead.

323
00:30:09,286 --> 00:30:11,804
They won’t disappear. I saved them for you.

324
00:30:12,664 --> 00:30:15,064
Just please don’t close the program.

325
00:30:15,306 --> 00:30:18,084
Oh. Okay.

326
00:30:20,067 --> 00:30:22,134
You’ve got potential, you know.

327
00:30:22,951 --> 00:30:25,444
If you ever change your mind about
pursuing the religious path,

328
00:30:25,469 --> 00:30:26,804
you could go into science.

329
00:30:27,013 --> 00:30:30,564
Or vocational college. Something practical.

330
00:30:30,973 --> 00:30:31,985
How does that sound?

331
00:30:32,441 --> 00:30:33,763
Let me finish Grade 12 first.

332
00:30:34,804 --> 00:30:36,484
I’m already too lazy for school as it is.

333
00:30:36,618 --> 00:30:37,811
Okay.

334
00:30:38,840 --> 00:30:41,571
Anyway, Tanrak,
how did you two become close?

335
00:30:41,776 --> 00:30:44,123
Oh, we’re not close.

336
00:30:44,908 --> 00:30:45,908
Huh?

337
00:30:46,726 --> 00:30:47,849
I just felt sorry for him.

338
00:30:48,116 --> 00:30:49,441
He had no friends.

339
00:30:58,057 --> 00:30:59,670
The Mass is ended.

340
00:30:59,901 --> 00:31:02,234
Go in peace.

341
00:31:03,923 --> 00:31:08,470
I will not fight alone

342
00:31:10,071 --> 00:31:15,690
You who conquered death and sin

343
00:31:16,097 --> 00:31:21,004
Walk right beside me

344
00:31:27,837 --> 00:31:28,837
Oh!

345
00:31:34,146 --> 00:31:35,150
Who are they?

346
00:31:35,951 --> 00:31:37,849
Cherry and Oh.

347
00:31:38,272 --> 00:31:39,836
Childhood friends from my neighborhood.

348
00:31:42,182 --> 00:31:43,184
Really just friends?

349
00:31:51,598 --> 00:31:53,484
Cherry. Oh.

350
00:31:55,443 --> 00:31:56,447
How have you been?

351
00:31:57,120 --> 00:31:59,844
This is Barth. He just joined in Grade 12.

352
00:32:01,360 --> 00:32:02,360
Hi.

353
00:32:03,436 --> 00:32:04,924
I’ll go put my things away.

354
00:32:09,846 --> 00:32:11,585
You haven’t been to church in ages.

355
00:32:11,724 --> 00:32:13,969
Yeah. I’ve been helping my mom at the shop.

356
00:32:14,530 --> 00:32:16,924
She’s been seeing the doctor,

357
00:32:17,323 --> 00:32:18,487
so I had to cover for her.

358
00:32:19,718 --> 00:32:21,398
Is Auntie Tim doing okay?

359
00:32:22,191 --> 00:32:23,195
She’s all right.

360
00:32:23,311 --> 00:32:24,321
Did you know?

361
00:32:24,411 --> 00:32:26,979
They’re building a 7-Eleven
where your house was.

362
00:32:30,210 --> 00:32:31,409
They tore it down?

363
00:32:34,578 --> 00:32:35,618
How long ago?

364
00:32:35,753 --> 00:32:36,781
It’s about to open.

365
00:32:36,948 --> 00:32:39,315
So quick how they demolished the house
and built the store.

366
00:32:42,094 --> 00:32:44,375
What about the rose apple tree next door?

367
00:32:45,553 --> 00:32:46,644
Is it still there?

368
00:32:48,324 --> 00:32:50,404
That tree died
before they even tore the house down.

369
00:32:53,575 --> 00:32:57,178
But do you remember
when we climbed that tree as kids?

370
00:32:57,998 --> 00:32:59,484
I fell, and it hurt like hell.

371
00:32:59,905 --> 00:33:03,364
My mom scolded me for a whole week.

372
00:33:06,901 --> 00:33:09,281
You seem a lot quieter now, Tanrak.

373
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:13,000
Really?

374
00:33:13,770 --> 00:33:15,636
Yeah. More grown-up.

375
00:33:19,290 --> 00:33:20,604
We should go.

376
00:33:21,265 --> 00:33:22,265
See you.

377
00:34:15,870 --> 00:34:17,241
You guys go ahead.

378
00:34:17,463 --> 00:34:19,079
See you.

379
00:34:47,200 --> 00:34:48,647
I wondered where you disappeared to.

380
00:34:50,712 --> 00:34:51,722
What are you doing?

381
00:34:57,391 --> 00:34:59,044
Practicing for the Christmas party.

382
00:35:03,934 --> 00:35:04,934
Play for me.

383
00:35:08,196 --> 00:35:09,196
Sure.

384
00:35:25,095 --> 00:35:26,775
I said I was practicing.

385
00:35:39,616 --> 00:35:40,616
Tanrak.

386
00:35:43,836 --> 00:35:45,811
If something’s stressing you out,
you can tell me.

387
00:35:46,607 --> 00:35:47,628
You know that, right?

388
00:35:51,456 --> 00:35:52,776
Come on. Teach me.

389
00:35:56,533 --> 00:35:57,541
How do you play?

390
00:35:57,994 --> 00:35:59,021
How do you play?

391
00:36:00,024 --> 00:36:02,564
Let’s start with… C.

392
00:36:07,454 --> 00:36:08,454
C, huh?

393
00:36:11,250 --> 00:36:12,535
-What else?
-B minor.

394
00:36:13,986 --> 00:36:15,244
-Like this?
-Yes.

395
00:36:29,549 --> 00:36:30,549
Barth.

396
00:36:33,358 --> 00:36:34,567
You’re such a tease.

397
00:36:36,768 --> 00:36:38,284
I never said I couldn’t play.

398
00:36:38,746 --> 00:36:39,959
I just wanted you to teach me.

399
00:36:50,660 --> 00:36:51,876
Out of all the chords,

400
00:36:52,226 --> 00:36:53,244
which one do you like?

401
00:36:55,362 --> 00:36:57,854
Well... they all sound nice, don’t they?

402
00:37:00,331 --> 00:37:03,484
No. Say you could choose only one chord

403
00:37:04,894 --> 00:37:05,941
for the rest of your life.

404
00:37:06,375 --> 00:37:07,397
Which one would it be?

405
00:37:10,295 --> 00:37:11,295
Probably...

406
00:37:14,022 --> 00:37:15,022
C.

407
00:37:26,582 --> 00:37:27,964
I thought you’d pick this one.

408
00:37:34,235 --> 00:37:35,275
It suits you.

409
00:37:37,704 --> 00:37:38,704
Really?

410
00:37:39,276 --> 00:37:41,404
So what note do you like?

411
00:37:45,036 --> 00:37:46,036
What note?

412
00:37:51,196 --> 00:37:52,196
This one.

413
00:38:01,544 --> 00:38:02,544
Why?

414
00:38:09,888 --> 00:38:10,888
It feels...

415
00:38:12,492 --> 00:38:13,532
out of place.

416
00:38:15,349 --> 00:38:16,684
Like it doesn’t belong.

417
00:38:19,656 --> 00:38:21,604
Like it’s somewhere it shouldn’t be.

418
00:38:35,787 --> 00:38:38,604
How about we play that song?

419
00:38:59,242 --> 00:39:02,676
There is a truth I want you to know

420
00:39:03,264 --> 00:39:06,674
Meanings many words seem to hold

421
00:39:07,348 --> 00:39:10,752
No matter how beautiful they may be

422
00:39:11,530 --> 00:39:14,330
They fall short of what you mean to me

423
00:39:14,984 --> 00:39:18,444
Everything I do for you

424
00:39:18,980 --> 00:39:22,444
May reflect what my heart holds true

425
00:39:23,003 --> 00:39:26,158
Maybe my eyes already show

426
00:39:26,207 --> 00:39:28,884
The feelings in my heart that flow

427
00:39:29,623 --> 00:39:36,690
But do you know it's so much more?

428
00:39:37,312 --> 00:39:42,571
Things I would like to give to you

429
00:39:45,844 --> 00:39:47,861
I’d gather every star

430
00:39:47,886 --> 00:39:51,484
To show all the love I have for you

431
00:39:51,807 --> 00:39:55,101
And make every song belong to you

432
00:39:55,251 --> 00:40:00,737
To tell you I love you more
than words could say

433
00:40:01,030 --> 00:40:02,568
Through seasons change

434
00:40:02,854 --> 00:40:08,657
I'll spend with you my every single breath

435
00:40:09,251 --> 00:40:12,174
No words can replace

436
00:40:12,584 --> 00:40:18,735
What my heart means
when it says I love you

437
00:40:19,427 --> 00:40:26,722
Let this love song speak for my heart
which belongs only to you

438
00:40:27,542 --> 00:40:33,584
Let it be the promise of our love
until the time is through

439
00:40:39,398 --> 00:40:41,249
I’d gather every star

440
00:40:41,376 --> 00:40:45,006
To show all the love I have for you

441
00:40:45,327 --> 00:40:48,647
And make every song belong to you

442
00:40:48,758 --> 00:40:54,297
To tell you I love you more
than words could say

443
00:40:54,572 --> 00:40:56,245
Through seasons change

444
00:40:56,400 --> 00:41:02,719
I'll spend with you my every single breath

445
00:41:02,873 --> 00:41:05,560
No words can replace

446
00:41:06,173 --> 00:41:13,067
What my heart means
when it says I love you

447
00:41:13,106 --> 00:41:18,347
If I speak in the tongues
of men or of angels

448
00:41:18,858 --> 00:41:20,010
but do not have love,

449
00:41:20,942 --> 00:41:24,972
I am only a resounding gong
or a clanging cymbal.

450
00:41:35,163 --> 00:41:36,189
Because we’re friends.

451
00:42:06,558 --> 00:42:07,558
Barth.

452
00:42:10,414 --> 00:42:11,567
What are you doing?

453
00:42:13,672 --> 00:42:15,017
I know who’s lying now.

454
00:42:18,156 --> 00:42:19,297
Lying about what?

455
00:42:20,720 --> 00:42:21,977
The brain teaser.

456
00:42:23,150 --> 00:42:24,977
The Lost One, the Lover, and the Believer.

457
00:42:26,245 --> 00:42:27,258
I figured it out.

458
00:42:28,664 --> 00:42:29,737
What’s the answer?

459
00:42:31,519 --> 00:42:33,132
-I think...
-Not ready to sleep yet, huh?

460
00:42:36,513 --> 00:42:37,682
Did it have to be now?

461
00:42:41,119 --> 00:42:42,297
I wanted to know now.

462
00:42:43,504 --> 00:42:44,504
Why?

463
00:42:46,176 --> 00:42:47,176
Why?

464
00:42:50,645 --> 00:42:53,619
Because now I’m being punished,
writing down saints’ names in the cemetery.

465
00:42:57,713 --> 00:42:58,713
Hey.

466
00:43:06,495 --> 00:43:07,935
Did you hear that?

467
00:43:08,815 --> 00:43:10,207
I heard a weird sound.

468
00:43:26,264 --> 00:43:27,359
You’re scared, aren’t you?

469
00:43:30,287 --> 00:43:31,665
Then go by yourself.

470
00:43:33,509 --> 00:43:34,566
You have to come with me.

471
00:43:34,591 --> 00:43:35,626
You’re being punished.

472
00:43:38,811 --> 00:43:40,385
There’s nothing there. Don’t be scared.

473
00:43:58,914 --> 00:44:01,305
Joanna Wattana.

474
00:44:06,514 --> 00:44:07,670
John the Baptist.

475
00:44:10,131 --> 00:44:12,905
Hey, that’s my saint’s name.

476
00:44:16,928 --> 00:44:18,375
What’s up, John the Baptist Tanrak?

477
00:44:23,143 --> 00:44:24,143
You know,

478
00:44:25,100 --> 00:44:27,964
Master Phak wouldn’t know
if we just made up saints’ names.

479
00:44:32,642 --> 00:44:34,362
Yeah. True.

480
00:44:36,094 --> 00:44:37,705
What does Master Phak even do all day

481
00:44:39,150 --> 00:44:40,823
besides catching us doing wrong things?

482
00:44:43,477 --> 00:44:44,964
Master Phak is a good person.

483
00:44:46,029 --> 00:44:47,872
He’s my spiritual mentor.

484
00:44:48,690 --> 00:44:50,905
He’s not actually that strict.

485
00:44:53,532 --> 00:44:55,027
If you become a Master one day,

486
00:44:56,522 --> 00:44:57,705
who’s gonna be scared of you?

487
00:45:01,021 --> 00:45:02,185
You look way too kind.

488
00:45:10,216 --> 00:45:11,216
Really?

489
00:45:16,005 --> 00:45:18,505
Nine... twenty.

490
00:45:20,791 --> 00:45:22,387
Done. Let’s go.

491
00:45:24,106 --> 00:45:25,106
Hey, wait.

492
00:45:28,484 --> 00:45:29,665
Since we’re already out,

493
00:45:31,062 --> 00:45:32,267
wanna sneak out for some roti?

494
00:45:40,024 --> 00:45:41,064
Don’t tell me

495
00:45:41,954 --> 00:45:43,385
you’ve never snuck out of school.

496
00:45:56,362 --> 00:45:58,185
Seriously? Come with me.

497
00:46:07,469 --> 00:46:08,477
Then hold this for me.

498
00:46:27,333 --> 00:46:28,970
It’s high. Give me a boost.

499
00:47:01,299 --> 00:47:02,579
One, two, three.

500
00:47:14,173 --> 00:47:15,217
You really won’t come?

501
00:47:15,851 --> 00:47:17,618
Come on. I’ll help you up.

502
00:47:36,042 --> 00:47:37,669
Then wait here. I’ll be back soon.

503
00:48:01,255 --> 00:48:06,265
Lust means letting desire control us.

504
00:48:06,993 --> 00:48:09,024
What if you can’t stop it?

505
00:48:27,334 --> 00:48:28,420
You really won’t come?

506
00:48:28,982 --> 00:48:31,105
Come on. I’ll help you up.

507
00:49:01,852 --> 00:49:04,404
Here. I bought this for you.

508
00:49:05,391 --> 00:49:06,391
Have some.

509
00:49:08,695 --> 00:49:10,492
Hurry up. I wanna sleep.

510
00:49:26,801 --> 00:49:27,801
Help me.

511
00:50:16,843 --> 00:50:17,843
Eat it.

512
00:50:51,318 --> 00:50:52,585
Hurry up. I need to pee.

513
00:50:56,311 --> 00:50:57,311
Here.

514
00:50:58,703 --> 00:50:59,703
Pee here.

515
00:51:02,106 --> 00:51:03,117
No need to be shy.

516
00:51:28,787 --> 00:51:29,787
Nice aim.

517
00:51:45,947 --> 00:51:47,281
The answer is the Lost One.

518
00:51:49,454 --> 00:51:51,286
Because the Lost One always tells the truth.

519
00:57:52,285 --> 00:57:57,073
When the human heart starts beating,
it naturally begins to seek love.

520
00:57:57,725 --> 00:57:58,725
Why?

521
00:57:58,882 --> 00:58:02,233
I just haven’t seen you smile in a long time.

522
00:58:06,342 --> 00:58:06,929
Barth!

523
00:58:06,954 --> 00:58:08,568
Barth is so cool.

524
00:58:08,961 --> 00:58:10,894
Do you think he likes Cherry?

525
00:58:11,163 --> 00:58:14,025
I don’t know if he likes her,
but Cherry definitely likes Barth.

526
00:58:14,221 --> 00:58:19,543
But the question is:
does every kind of love bring us closer to Him?

